Class COERSequenceOf

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.asn1.coer.COERSequenceOf
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, COEREncodable, Encodable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PermissibleCrls, PolygonalRegion, SequenceOfCertificate, SequenceOfGroupCrlEntry, SequenceOfHashBasedRevocationInfo, SequenceOfHashedId3, SequenceOfHashedId8, SequenceOfIdentifiedRegion, SequenceOfIMaxGroup, SequenceOfIndividualRevocation, SequenceOfJMaxGroup, SequenceOfLAGroup, SequenceOfOctetString, SequenceOfPsid, SequenceOfPsidGroupPermissions, SequenceOfPsidSsp, SequenceOfPsidSspRange, SequenceOfRecipientInfo, SequenceOfRectangularRegion, SequenceOfRegionAndSubregions, SequenceOfUint16, SequenceOfUint8

    public class COERSequenceOf
extends java.lang.Object
implements COEREncodable
    The encoding of a sequence-of value shall consist of a quantity field followed by the encodings of the occurrences of the component (of the same type and constraints).

    For more information see ISO/IEC 8825-7:2015 Section 17

    See Also:
